code.title: Functional group response
code.desc: To identify a functional group in the subject interchange and to indicate acknowledgement or rejection (action taken) of the UNG and UNE segments, and to identify any error related to these segments. Depending on the action code, it may also indicate the action taken on the messages within that functional group.

code.title: Interchange response
code.desc: To identify the subject interchange, to indicate interchange receipt, to indicate acknowledgement or rejection (action taken) of the UNA, UNB and UNZ segments, and to identify any error related to these segments. Depending on the action code, it may also indicate the action taken on the functional groups and messages within that interchange.

code.title: Message response
code.desc: To identify a message in the subject interchange, and to indicate that message's acknowledgement or rejection (action taken), and to identify any error related to the UNH and UNT segments.

code.title: Segment error indication
code.desc: To identify either a segment containing an error or a missing segment, and to identify any error related to the complete segment.

code.title: Service string advice
code.desc: To define the characters selected for use as delimiters and indicators in the rest of the interchange that follows.

data_element.name: first/lastSequenceMessageTransferIndication
data_element.desc: Indication used for the first and last message in a sequence of the same type of message relating to the same topic.

code.title: Creation
code.desc: First transmission of a number of transfers of the same message.

code.title: Final
code.desc: Last transmission of a number of transfers of the same message.

data_element.name: sectionIdentification
data_element.desc: A character identifying the next section in a message.

code.title: Header/detail section separation
code.desc: To qualify the segment UNS, when separating the header from the detail section of a message.

code.title: Detail/summary section separation
code.desc: To qualify the segment UNS, when separating the detail from the summary section of a message.

data_element.name: action,Coded
data_element.desc: A code indicating acknowledgement, or rejection (the action taken) of a subject interchange, or part of the subject interchange.

code.title: This level and all lower levels rejected
code.desc: The corresponding referenced-level and all its lower referenced-levels are rejected. One or more errors are reported at this reporting-level or a lower reporting- level.

code.title: This level acknowledged, next lower level acknowledged if not explicitly rejected
code.desc: The corresponding referenced-level is acknowledged. All messages or functional groups at the next lower referenced-level are acknowledged except those explicitly reported as rejected at the next lower reporting-level in this CONTRL message.

code.title: Interchange received
code.desc: Indication of interchange receipt implies that the recipient of the subject interchange: has received the interchange; and acknowledges the parts of the interchange that have been checked in order to assure that the data elements copied into the reporting UCI segment are syntactically correct; and has accepted liability for notifying the sender of acknowledgement or rejection of the other parts of the interchange; and has taken reasonable precautions in order to ensure that the sender is so notified.

data_element.name: syntaxError,Coded
data_element.desc: A code indicating the syntax error detected.

code.title: Syntax version or level not supported
code.desc: Notification that the syntax version and/or level is not supported by the recipient.

code.title: Interchange recipient not actual recipient
code.desc: Notification that the Interchange recipient (S003) is different from the actual recipient.

code.title: Invalid value
code.desc: Notification that the value of a simple data element, composite data element or component data element does not conform to the relevant specifications for the value.

code.title: Missing
code.desc: Notification that a mandatory (or otherwise required) service or user segment, data element, composite data element or component data element is missing

code.title: Value not supported in this position
code.desc: Notification that the recipient does not support use of the specific value of an identified simple data element, composite data element or component data element in the position where it is used. The value may be valid according to the relevant specifications and may be supported if it is used in another position.

code.title: Not supported in this position
code.desc: Notification that the recipient does not support use of the segment type, simple data element type, composite data element type or component data element type in the specific in the identified position.

code.title: Too many constituents
code.desc: Notification that the identified segment contained too many data elements or that the identified composite data element contained too many component data elements.

code.title: No agreement
code.desc: No agreement exist that allows receipt of an interchange, functional group or message with the value of the identified simple data element, composite data element or component data element.

code.title: Unspecified error
code.desc: Notification that an error has been identified, but the nature of the error is not reported.

code.title: Invalid decimal notation
code.desc: Notification that the character indicated as decimal notation in UNA is invalid, or the decimal notation used in a data element is not consistent with the one indicated in UNA.

code.title: Character invalid as service character
code.desc: Notification that a character advised in UNA is invalid as service character.

code.title: Invalid character(s)
code.desc: Notification that one or more character(s) used in the interchange is not a valid character as defined by the syntax level indicated in UNB. The invalid character is part of the referenced-level, or followed immediately after the identified part of the interchange.

code.title: Invalid service character(s)
code.desc: Notification that the service character(s) used in the interchange is not a valid service character as advised in UNA or not one of the service characters in the syntax level indicated in UNB or defined in an interchange agreement. If the code is used in UCS or UCD, the invalid character followed immediately after the identified part of the interchange.

code.title: Unknown Interchange sender
code.desc: Notification that the Interchange sender (S002) is unknown.

code.title: Too old
code.desc: Notification that the received interchange or functional group is older than a limit specified in an IA or determined by the recipient.

code.title: Test indicator not supported
code.desc: Notification that a test processing could not be performed for the identified interchange, functional group or message.

code.title: Duplicate detected
code.desc: Notification that a possible duplication of a previously received interchange, functional group or message has been detected. The earlier transmission may have been rejected.

code.title: Security function not supported
code.desc: Notification that a security function related to the referenced-level or data element is not supported.

code.title: References do not match
code.desc: Notification that the control reference in UNB/UNG/UNH does not match the one in UNZ/UNE/UNT.

code.title: Control count does not match number of instances received
code.desc: Notification that the number of functional groups/ messages/segments does not match the number given in UNZ/UNE/UNT.

code.title: Functional groups and messages mixed
code.desc: Notification that individual messages and functional groups have been mixed at the same level in the interchange.

code.title: More than one message type in group
code.desc: Notification that different message types are contained in a functional group.

code.title: Lower level empty
code.desc: Notification that the interchange did not contain any messages or functional groups, or a functional group did not contain any messages.

code.title: Invalid occurrence outside message or functional group
code.desc: Notification that an invalid segment or data element occurred in the interchange, between messages or between functional groups. Rejection is reported at the level above.

code.title: Nesting indicator not allowed
code.desc: Notification that explicit nesting has been used in a message where it shall not be used.

code.title: Too many segment repetitions
code.desc: Notification that a segment was repeated too many times.

code.title: Too many segment group repetitions
code.desc: Notification that a segment group is repeated to many times.

code.title: Invalid type of character(s)
code.desc: Notification that one or more numeric characters were used in an alphabetic (component) data element or that one or more alphabetic characters were used in a numeric (component) data element.

code.title: Missing digit in front of decimal sign
code.desc: Notification that a decimal sign is not preceded by one or more digits.

code.title: Data element too long
code.desc: Notification that the length of the data element received exceeded the maximum length specified in the data element description.

code.title: Data element too short
code.desc: Notification that the length of the data element received is shorter than the minimum length specified in the data element description.

code.title: Permanent communication network error
code.desc: Notification that a permanent error was reported by the communication network used for transfer of the interchange. Re-transmission of an identical interchange with the same parameters at network level will not succeed.

code.title: Temporary communication network error
code.desc: Notification that a temporary error was reported by the communication network used for transfer of the interchange. Re-transmissions of an identical interchange may succeed.

code.title: Unknown interchange recipient
code.desc: Notification that the interchange recipient is not known by a network provider.
